  "local_port": 46670,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some best resume?",
  "response": "Creating a standout resume involves tailored content, clear formatting, and effective branding. Here are some best practices for crafting an excellent resume:\n\n### 1. **Choose the Right Format**\n   - **Chronological:** Lists work experience in reverse chronological order. Ideal for those with a solid employment history.\n   - **Functional:** Focuses on skills and experiences rather than chronological work history. Good for career changers or those with gaps in employment.\n   - **Combination:** Blends both chronological and functional formats, showcasing skills while also providing a chronological work history.\n\n### 2. **Craft a Strong Header**\n   - Include your name, phone number, email address, and LinkedIn profile (if applicable).\n   - Ensure your email address sounds professional.\n\n### 3. **Write a Compelling Summary or Objective**\n   - A summary briefly highlights your key qualifications and career achievements.\n   - An objective states your career goals and what you hope to achieve in the position.\n\n### 4. **Highlight Key Skills**\n   - Include a mix of hard and soft skills relevant to the job.\n   - Use keywords from the job description to pass through Applicant Tracking Systems (ATS).\n\n### 5. **Detail Your Work Experience**\n   - List your jobs in reverse chronological order.\n   - Use bullet points for clarity, starting each with action verbs (e.g., \"Managed,\" \"Developed,\" \"Implemented\").\n   - Quantify achievements when possible (e.g., \"Increased sales by 20% within one year\").\n\n### 6. **Education Section**\n   - Include your highest degree first, along with the institution and graduation date.\n   - Optionally, include relevant coursework, honors, or academic achievements.\n\n### 7. **Certifications and Additional Training**\n   - List any relevant certifications or professional development that pertains to the job.\n\n### 8. **Incorporate a Projects or Achievements Section**\n   - Include personal or professional projects that demonstrate relevant skills or competencies.\n\n### 9. **Keep it Concise and Relevant**\n   - Aim for one page, or two pages if you have extensive experience.\n   - Remove any information that doesn\u2019t directly relate to the job you\u2019re applying for.\n\n### 10. **Use Professional Formatting**\n   - Select a clean, professional font (e.g., Arial, Calibri, Times New Roman).\n   - Use consistent formatting for headings and bullet points.\n   - Ensure there is plenty of white space for easier reading.\n\n### 11. **Proofread**\n   - Check for spelling and grammar errors.\n   - Consider having someone else review your resume for feedback.\n\n### 12. **Tailor Your Resume for Each Job Application**\n   - Adjust the summary, skills, and experience sections to align with the specific job description.\n   - This can significantly improve your chances of landing an interview.\n\n### Resume Examples\n- **Corporate Resume:** A traditional format focusing on work experience, education, and key skills.\n- **Creative Resume:** Visually appealing with unique design elements, ideal for industries like design or marketing.\n- **Technical Resume:** Highlights technical skills and projects, often used in IT and engineering fields.\n\nBy applying these best practices, you can create a powerful resume that effectively showcases your qualifications and improves your chances of landing an interview.",
